CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1970, pg. 15 reads:" New Pittsburgh Links- Nine charming young women were installed in Pittsburgh Chapter of Links, Inc. at the home of Link Elizabeth Youngue recently. The lush blooming garden of the Youngue's Squirrel Hill home made a fitting background for the handsome maids and matrons, who have now joined the Nation wide chain of Links.  Link Lucille Cuthbert installed the newcomers.  Link Norine Cyrus is president.  In the group of new members shown here are: Miss Laura Cooper, Mrs. Barbara (Wilson) Allen, Mrs. Helen (Robert) Smith, Mrs. Helen (George) Shields, Mrs. Joan (James), Mrs. Helen (William B.) Miller, Mrs. Nan (Robert E.) Currington and Mrs. Alice (Earle Belle) Smith."
TitMainTitle: Members of Pittsburgh Chapter of Links, Inc., possibly including Laura Cooper, Barbara Allen, Helen Smith, Helen Shields, Ms. Joan, Helen Miller, Nan Moone Currington, and Alice Smith standing in yard of home of Elizabeth Youngue, Squirrel Hill
